      "content": "That sounds pretty rough. I've been hearing a lot of stuff online too, but a lot of it seems so one-sided. Some people say it's just about fairness and helping people live better, but you make it sound like it's mostly just a death sentence for small shops. Is there any actual data that shows it might actually help the local economy in the long run, or is that just a theory?",
